  "answer": "The work is **Kalpabuddha** (author unknown), **Chapter 1**.[^1]\n\nThe cosmogonic opening states verbatim: \"Lord Buddha was in the great dissolution (`mahāpralaya`), his body came into being, he then became the Lord Pañcatathāgata.\"[^2]\n\nThe central Tathāgata's attributes are described verbatim as: \"his `mudrā` is the `bodhyagrī`, his `jñāna` is `śāśvata`, his implement is the `cakra`. Sahāvatī is the name of his dominion, a lion is his mount.\" He is accompanied by \"She, Lady Sattvavajrī, she, Lady Dharmavajrī, she, Lady Karmavajrī, they are the `devī`s accompanying him.\"[^2]\n\n[^1]: Unknown, *Kalpabuddha*, Chapter 1, [/works/unknown-kalpabuddha-d760dc/01/translation/](https://falsafa.corpus/works/unknown-kalpabuddha-d760dc/01/translation/).\n\n[^2]: Unknown, *Kalpabuddha*, Chapter 1, [paragraph](/works/unknown-kalpabuddha-d760dc/01/translation/#p-e1c8df).",
